{"id":"drink-strong","term":"Drink, strong","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(Heb. shekar’), an intoxicating liquor (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 13:4\">Judg. 13:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 1:15\">Luke 1:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 5:11\">Isa. 5:11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Micah 2:11\">Micah 2:11</a>) distilled from corn, honey, or dates. The effects of the use of strong drink are referred to in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 107:27\">Ps. 107:27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 24:20\">Isa. 24:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 49:26\">49:26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 51:17\">51:17-22</a>. Its use prohibited, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 20:1\">Prov. 20:1</a>. (See WINE.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Judges 13:4","Luke 1:15","Isaiah 5:11","Micah 2:11","Psalms 107:27","Isaiah 24:20","Isaiah 49:26","Isaiah 51:17","Proverbs 20:1"]}